        "notes": "MEDIUM priority - only worth it when BOTH faces of the cut show. True compression (up+down), NO bearing. EU verified 2026-07-16: W02504, 6mm dia / 8mm shank / 24mm cutting length / 75mm OVL, 2FL. EUR 49.16 uncoated or EUR 51.21 SPE-X. 8mm shank uses the Kress's included 8mm collet. IMPORTANT technique: with light 2mm stepdowns a compression bit behaves like an upcut - the top edge is cut on the first shallow pass by the UPCUT tip, so the top face frays and you never use the downcut half. To get clean-both-faces you MUST: rough with light passes leaving ~0.4mm radial (Stock to Leave), then ONE full-depth finishing pass at 0 stock so both zones engage the whole wall at once. For hidden-bottom work (shelves, spoilboard-backed), the #1 downcut is simpler and cleaner - buy this only when you have both-faces-show parts."
